The paper discusses a framework for efficient access and processing of Web archive data, which involves information retrieval (IR) techniques for searching and extracting relevant data, as well as database (DB) and distributed computing (CR) aspects for scalability. The focus on usability and integration with external tools suggests a human-computer interaction (HC) component.
